    <div align="left">
	<hr align="left" width="100%" />

    <!-- message -->
    <div align="left" id="post_message_295855">I was sitting around reading about Shadow Hearts and I came up with a campaign hook. *GURPS is base system*<br />
The players make standard GURPS heros based in the modern age. An angel appears to the players and bestows a mission upon them: SAVE THE WORLD FROM DARKNESS! *standard video game/ anime / campaign plot alert*<br />
Here's the hook. The darkness/devil/hell are winning the fight and time is running out. There are too few warriors who fight for good, so the angel has a plan, fight fire with fire! As an important angel in the army of heaven he can enter hell with impunity. As such he can remove souls from hell and bring them back to life to fight for him. However, only one character can be removed from hell at a time, if more are removed than the darkness will know something is up. So, the players can summon one NPC from hell at a time to help them fight the good fight. <br />
I plan on making players need to enter the pysche of npc and convince him/her to join them. In exchange for helping the players the NPCs will be pardoned from hell.<br />
 <br />
I only want to use famous historical figures(who might be in hell) in the game, that is Genghis Khan, Vlad the Impaler, Al Capone, etc.<br />
I want gameplay to be sorta realistic but cinematic. Think Metal Gear: Solid or Cowboy Bebop.<br />
 <br />
Basically, here is where I need help.<br />
I need a better underlying plot. Who are the players? The devil? Something else? God? Angels? Also, why are only famous historial available? Who is the final bad guy, what is the final fight?<br />
I really like the game hook of creating a stable of historical figures who you can summon to fight for you. I just need to work on the underlying plot.<br />
I also need characters to use in the game, it would be awesome if they could be put down into gurps character sheets, but even simple explanations would be cool.<br />
I'll appreciate any ideas you can shoot my way.</div>
    <!-- / message -->
    
    
    <br>
